50|$|Lepidium campestre (<b>field</b> <b>pepperwort</b> or field pepperweed) is {{an annual}} {{plant in the}} Brassicaceae or mustard family, native to Europe, but {{commonly}} found in North America as an invasive weed. The most notable characteristic of field pepperweed is the raceme of flowers which forks off of the stem. These racemes {{are made up of}} first small white flowers and later green, flat and oval seedpods each about 6 mm long and 4 mm wide. Each seedpod contains two brown, 2.5 mm long seeds.|$|E

